<br>
Yup, QA is vastly different from being a &quot;tester.&quot;   There is definitely an art to QA.  It's more then just random testing...there is SO much methodology you can learn.<br>
<br>
I don't know about game companies (sorry this doesn't answer your question directly, but maybe this will give you an idea), but where I work entry level for QA is twice that of minimum wage, and there is definitely room to grow.  We have 2 tracks:<br>
<br>
QA Analyst - Less technical of the QA.  More about method, statistics and planning.  Generally, analysts move into lead positions and product management.<br>
<br>
QA Engineer - More technical.  They write test tools and harnesses.  A lot of them move into Dev eventually.<br>
<br>
Even if QAers don't move into Dev or management, there is a decent living to be made.  QA Contractors with experience make upwards of $25 an hour. <p>Vazaelle wizard and member of the <a href = http://www.ogzr.org> Ancients of the Realm. </a>   <br> <a href = http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=10989> Magelo. </a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/uwhizbangdustyboots.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Whizbang Dustyboots</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>O.G. (Original Gnome)</span><br>  Posts: 997<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/12/02 7:17:55 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2355.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.lby3.com/eq/whiz/flappy.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Game Industry</span><hr size=1> Yow. Most of our QA grunts are driving cars as old as me, or have parents/roommates/girlfriends dropping them off. Not much money, but the number of big deal producers who started off in their position keeps them coming back. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/usaxmoore.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Saxmoore</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 30<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/12/02 8:17:51 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2355.topic&index=14>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Game Industry</span><hr size=1> Interesting.  I guess it's good to see the comparison.  I also guess I'll be staying in consumer/enterprise software, hehe.  <p>Vazaelle wizard and member of the <a href = http://www.ogzr.org> Ancients of the Realm. </a>   <b